    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Disturbance of soil and sediment by flora or fauna; in an archaeological context, bioturbation serves to displace and move buried artifacts such as grave goods.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
